<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-92-0239 </DOCNO><TEXT>Public Law 97-414, the Orphan Drug Act, passed by Congress and enactedon Jan. 4, 1983, directed the Secretary of HHS to construct radioepidemiologicaltables showing the probability that certain cancers could result fromprior exposure to radiation. The Ad Hoc Working Group together with severalother organizations collaborated to establish the tables.</TEXT></DOC>